<title>USA: Regeneron Pharm Q1 net loss narrows.</title>
<headline>Regeneron Pharm Q1 net loss narrows.</headline>
<dateline>TARRYTOWN, N.Y. 1997-05-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Three months</p>
<p>							Ended March 31,</p>
<p>							1997	    1996</p>
<p> Revenues				     6,213,635     5,188,669</p>
<p> Net loss				  ( 5,928,849)  ( 7,767,498)</p>
<p> Net loss per share			   ( 0.23)	 ( 0.35)</p>
<p>Weighted average number of Common</p>
<p>  and Class A shares outstanding     25,798,971    22,007,864</p>
<p>NOTE:  Full name of the company is Regeneron Pharmaceuticals Inc.  </p>
<p>Total operating expenses were $12.1 million in the first quarter of 1997 as compared with $13.0 million in the first quarter of 1996.  The company said this decrease was due primarily to a reduction in its share of loss in Amgen-Regeneron Partners, as the partnership completed the Phase III clinical trial of BDNF in 1996.</p>
</text>
